<Author>dmlandis
<Content>OK property to spend a few nights Hotel Fontan was an average property. Great location - 1/2 a block from Hidalgo Metro station as well as Avenida Juarez and Alameda Park. My room was quiet but sparsely furnished. There was a comfortable enough bed but no clock radio or city information. The hallways were dark and there was maintenance on the elevators. The rooms could definitely be upgraded and have more amenities put in. On the plus side, the breakfast buffer (99 pesos) was very good with great selection of fruits, entrees, etc. 
