<Author>viajera511
<Content>Horrendous experience, couldn't wait to leave The best thing that this hotel has going for it is its location. It is right next to the Hidalgo Metro and walking distance from the Alameda Central, Palacio de Bellas Artes, and Zocalo in the historic district of Mexico City. The restaurant is also very good, with excellent service and a delicious breakfast (included). However, staying here requires so much patience and the incompetent and unhelpful hotel staff make staying here an absolute nightmare. The room was clean enough, but because you are located on Mexico City's main boulevard, there is a constant roar outside that makes it very hard to sleep soundly. We had issues with our bathroom plumbing and it took 3 days for them to change our rooms. The most frustrating aspect of the hotel is that you are unable to make outside phone calls. You have to call the operator and tell her the number you want to call and she will make the call for you. This system is inefficient and archaic. She continuously put me on hold and took 10-15 minutes to even dial the number. Sometimes she took down the number wrong, so I had to call back and repeat it. Meanwhile, you are being charged for all the wrong numbers, whether or not it's your fault. It took a full day for me to find a way to make an emergency-related international call from the hotel and finally I had to sit with the operator at her desk and dial from there. The staff was unable to understand and respond to the urgency of my situation. They were unapologetic and unhelpful.I will say that the hotel was also hosting members of a huge international conference during my stay, so they were stretched, but given the nature of all the other reviews, I would say that it's safe to say that this hotel is one that everyone should pass on. 
