<Author>Meg4805
<Content>The worst hotel I have ever stayed in If you want comfort, service, or standard amenities, DO NOT stay at the Hotel Fontan.I have just returned from a 7 night stay - the only reason I did not check out and go elsewhere was because it had been booked and paid for through a tour operator.Check in took 25 minutes - when I was finally shown to my extremely basic, small room I discovered that it did not have any of the amenities one associates with a large city hotel. It did not have:- a hair dryer (and the front desk could not provide one)- an iron or an ironing board (and management would not provide these)- a safe deposit box - a clock radio/alarm - and when reception was asked for wake up calls, they got the time wrong - by an hour- 4 days out of 7.- tissues, any printed material about hotel services or mexico cityThe housekeeping was erratic - sometimes you had towels or toilet paper - sometimes not. Sometimes your room had been serviced when you returned at 5pm - sometimes not. The street noise was incredible - and windows were not double glazed - in fact,there were gaps around the seals, so the sound made you feel as if you were out there in all that traffic. The beds were rock hard - and management, unlike in other mexican hotels, did not have any rubber overlays.Public areas were dirty, staff in the restuarant were unhrelpful, and the food provided (apart from the buffet breakfast) was really bad 
