<Author>DriveGoddess
<Content>I can dig this joint yes I can Well I had booked this hotel before I even checked the reviews and after reading them they sort of smacked of amateur travelers who did not know much about hotels outside of their particular comfort zones. This is my second night here - I have one more night and because there is so much to do here I may add an extra night, space permitting. I recommend folks to try to get a room on the eighth floor, balcony section because it does have views of Alameda Park and that crazy horse sculpture on Reforma. I have nice hot water and I can get the net via my wireless. Now I had to cajole the good folks who work here to get a password, the manager came to my room to see that yes I could get a connection so he set me up good. This hotel is yes, dated decor wise but I am not staying here for the decor. The free breakfast hits the spot and nearby are good cheap eats, a farmacia, a convenience store, a Sanborns and of course the main drag, Reforma which is interesting in itself.The TV has some english channels and CNN and Fox in english. For the price and location you do quite well. This hotel attracts business travelers and as one I have found the staff to be very helpful especially since I walk with a cane and have a hard time getting around. I have stayed in all sorts of hotel worldwide and I would stay here again just because of the staff. Very conscientious folks indeed. Heck, not a bad place at all. I take most reviews with a grain of salt but when I read the negative ones I had to respond from my seasoned perspective. Thanks for allowing me this opportunity. 
