<Author>gsbpt
<Content>Wouln't recommend it For the price I paid was ok. I wouldn't go back anyway. I stayed there 5 days on holiday with my boyfriend, we didn't have hot water many times, the room was small and old fashioned, but at the end we just sleeped there. At the front desk not really friendly. The buffet was ok, friendly waiters. The most impressive part of the staff were the bell boys, they went one night to find a bottle of wine for us and even cigaretts and they brought them to our room (for a quite big tip anyway).If you are there to visit the town, outside the hotel there's always Ubaldo, it's a 50 years old man that is like a tour guide. It's not cheap, but he brings you where you want and he explains you everything. Or instead there is an office in the hotel that sells trips, not too expensive. 
