<Author>happyberks
<Content>checked out within 2 hours! We arrived and it took us 15 minutes to check-in. The process was very simple complete the form and get your key but as soon as a Mexican walked into reception we were ignored until they were assisted. When we arrived on our floor the lights were not on but discovered that they were on a sensor, which is good for the environment but not good for guests who have rooms down the end of the corridor because when you leave your room you have to walk back to the lift in darkness before you can trip the only sensor! I could open my door with my colleagues key we accidentally discovered much to our horror. The room itself was very dated, if you like very bright pink then maybe it is for you but the paint has been slapped onto very old wallpaper so you can image the quality of the finish. The furniture was basic to say the least and the bed was a disgrace. The toilet bowl was cracked as was the sink. But the worst point was that the window was single glazed, the window latch was broken so the window couldn't close and we were on a very busy street ( I know they are all busy in Mexico City! ). There is no air conditioning and in you want to use their wireless facility you need to be on either the 3rd or 9th floor! They also have no safes in the room and the TV reception is non-existent. We exited the hotel very quickly to find another local hotel and finally found a room at the local Sheritan (I can highly recommend this one!) before heading back to the Fontan to check out. On our way back up to our rooms we got stuck in the lift for 10 minutes, fortunately a member of staff was in there with us and could radio for help!!!This hotel did not feel safe - the windows wouldn't shut, you could open rooms with the wrong keys and their was no safe - for a city with such high crime we did not feel safe.If you are travelling to Mexico city do not book here, if you already have booked it cancel now! 
