<Author>Bookistan
<Content>This is a dump. I had to stay here when I was doing a project under the auspices of a Mexican cultural agency; they must get these rooms for next to nothing. It is a bit seedy and fairly rundown. My room looked out to a courtyard which was a surreal looking construction site. It was best to keep the drapes closed at all times. I don't think the decor has changed since maybe the 1970s. I had to pay a deposit to get a remote control to use with the tiny, cheap TV. I need a blow drier for my hair and the bathroom was not equipped with one. When I asked to borrow one at the front desk they send that the few they had were all checked out; they discouraged me from checking back. The restaurant was fairly cheerful; mostly buffet style. The food was OK, certainly more than edible, and the best part of staying there (which really isn't saying much). The location is also decent - on one end of the Reforma near Alameda Park. If you are on a budget you can find better places cheaper - BEWARE, do not stay here! 
